messages.content: What is the purpose of LiamUtil?
LiamUtil is a utility library developed for ComfyUI to provide useful tools and functionalities.
LiamLoadImage is a tool in LiamUtil that allows easy loading of images stored in OSS when using API interfaces.
How does ComfyUI load images by default?
By default, ComfyUI loads images from the Input folder.
What is shown in the example workflow image?
The example workflow image shows how to use LiamLoadImage to load an image in ComfyUI.
How can the example workflow be loaded into ComfyUI?
The example workflow can be loaded into ComfyUI by dragging the provided image into the ComfyUI application.
What is the file format of the example workflow image?
The example workflow image is in the JPEG format.
What is the file name of the example workflow image?
The file name of the example workflow image is 'out.jpeg'.
